WITH his coffin draped in Mzansi’s flag, mourners said a tearful goodbye to the great poet yesterday. Keorapetse “Bra Willie” Kgositsile’s funeral service at Marks Park in Emmarentia, Joburg was attended by a number of celebrities and politicians. Mourners included Sipho Hotstix Mabuse, Jonas Gwangwa and Lebogang Mashile, who paid tribute to Bra Willie with a poem. He died at Milpark Hospital two weeks ago after a short illness. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvscQzcNJD3ood0Sg9EvfjdqCxwygNzztXhFLrYSyxYufNwR101MKmT6n5L-kVPoFZX4UFm1uBg8CBCP03BVy2Oq6Lpg9aQYE8GtcYmyyO41FC8afYgLseLRQxCn5XZQ07mtxgKU4HC_m3g4bsteDTnN3s7FV8jCyzi41qDP7gw3Qfq0P36ne92G_2zExny8w_u1w8BMVQhUmbHNw313vpp9HAJ0HVd9gUDphkhFjjwMFtIEiwbRyY6LLde0aeSM2p86vW0pVn-ndiCj7-U-x4B6BwUOTA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzHqobs2i47suEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
